execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/dns-beta-measurement.md:14:Compute U_k for k = 0, 1, ..., K_max from DNS velocity fields. Fit log(U_k) = a*k + beta * log(U_{k-1}) via least squares. Requires: computing |u| on grid, level set truncations v_k, gradient norms d_k, supremum + integral for U_k. All standard L^p norms on periodic domains. **E002 result: 21 cases (5 ICs x 3-4 Re x 2 resolutions). All beta_eff < 4/3. Maximum beta_eff = 1.01 (ABC, Re=1000). See `dns-beta-empirical-results.md` for full data.** Critical design choice: L^inf normalization required (L^2 normalization makes level sets trivially empty for smooth flows).
