execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:23:### Why P_k^{21} is the bottleneck
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:25:The pressure P_k^{21} satisfies -Delta P_k^{21} = Sum_{i,j} partial_i partial_j [phi_k u_j(1 - v_k/|u|) u_i(1 - v_k/|u|)]. The factors u(1-v_k/|u|) are BOUNDED BY 1 (Lemma 10), so the RHS is bounded independently of U_{k-1}. By CZ/Riesz: ||P_k^{21}||_{L^q} <= C_q. No additional power of U_{k-1} can be extracted.
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:27:The non-divergence term gives:
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:29:int int |P_k^{21}| * |div(u*v_k/|u|)| dx dt  <=  ||P_k^{21}||_{L^q} * ||d_k||_{L^2} * ||1_{v_k>0}||_{L^{2q/(q-2)}}
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:32:Combined exponent: 1/2 + 5(q-2)/(6q) = 4/3 - 5/(3q), approaching 4/3 from below as q -> inf.
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:36:**The pressure is not small even when the velocity is close to its level set truncation.** P_k^{21} contributes U_{k-1}^0 = 1 to the exponent, while all other terms contribute at least U_{k-1}^{1/2}.
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:40:The gap is 1/6 = 3/2 - 4/3. This is NOT "small" in perturbation theory terms — it represents a qualitative failure where the current method cannot extract enough nonlinearity from the pressure's interaction with the level sets. The 4/3 bound is also NOT tight; it comes from worst-case Holder pairings.
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/beta-current-value-four-thirds.md:44:1. Better pressure regularity for P_k^{21} (beyond generic CZ)
