execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:3:Vasseur's 2007 De Giorgi approach to Navier-Stokes partial regularity (NoDEA 14:753-785). The framework defines a nonlinear recurrence U_k <= C^k * U_{k-1}^{beta_p} on level set energy quantities. The exponent beta_p controls regularity: beta > 1 gives partial regularity (CKN), beta > 3/2 would give full regularity. Current proof achieves beta < 4/3. The bottleneck is a single term: the non-divergence part of the local pressure P_k^{21}. **28 entries.** (NEW: vasseur-pressure S2-E008 — **Chebyshev bound PROVABLY TIGHT for div-free fields** (constant field u=(c,0,0) achieves ratio->1); all 4 De Giorgi chain steps individually confirmed tight under NS constraints; beta = 4/3 SHARP (rigorous) within De Giorgi-Vasseur framework; SDP formalization unnecessary — analytic extremizer is elementary; open question from S2-E001/S2-E003 (div-free level-set distribution) RESOLVED; 4 existing entries updated. Prior: S2-E007 adversarial review, S2-E006 non-CZ pressure routes, S2-E005 LP obstruction, S2-E002 DNS level-set distribution, S2-E004 compensated compactness, S2-E003 Chebyshev universality, S2-E001 sharpness audit, E010 near-Beltrami definitive negative, E009 adversarial, E007 Beltrami deficit truncation, E008 vorticity/H^1, E005 CV14, E006 Beltrami, E004 CZ slack.)
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:9:- **beta-current-value-four-thirds.md** — Current best beta < 4/3. Bottleneck is the non-divergence local pressure term P_k^{21}, with exponent 4/3 - 5/(3q) -> 4/3 as q -> inf. All other terms achieve 5/3 (well above 3/2). Gap of 1/6 is qualitative, not perturbative. Four possible routes to close the gap identified. [VERIFIED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:11:- **dns-beta-measurement.md** — Three approaches for empirically measuring beta from DNS: direct iteration measurement (fit U_k recurrence) **[TESTED E002]**, bottleneck term measurement (isolate P_k^{21} integral) **[TESTED E002]**, CZ slack proxy **[TESTED E004, ELIMINATED]**. Partially computable: ~10-15 De Giorgi levels on a 512^3 grid. Answer: empirical beta does NOT exceed 4/3 for any tested case. [PROVISIONAL → partially VERIFIED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:12:- **dns-beta-empirical-results.md** — **NEW (E002).** Full DNS measurement results: 5 ICs x 4 Re x 2 resolutions. All beta_eff < 4/3 (max 1.01 for ABC at Re=1000). Strong IC dependence: ABC (0.90-1.01) >> RandomGauss (0.35-0.39). Critical caveat: beta_eff != beta_p (different quantities). **E009: smooth-solution tautology — beta_eff < 4/3 is expected for smooth flows and proves nothing about analytical bound tightness. Measurement survives as empirical fact; interpretation does NOT.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:13:- **bottleneck-exponent-dns.md** — **NEW (E002).** Bottleneck exponent gamma (I_k ~ U_{k-1}^gamma) for the pressure integral P_k^{21}. Gamma DECREASES with Re for ALL ICs. At Re>=500, most ICs show gamma < 1. ABC maintains gamma > 1.1 (Beltrami structure). **E009: DNS evidence cannot diagnose near-singular bounds; gap genuineness supported by analytical/sociological evidence, not DNS.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:15:- **cz-slack-k-independent.md** — **NEW (E004).** CZ tightness ratio for P_k^{21} converges to a k-independent constant by k ~ 3-4. FALSIFIES hypothesis that CZ slack could improve beta. **E009: measurement on wrong regime — smooth flows, not near-singular. Survives as empirical fact, not as evidence about analytical bound tightness.** [VERIFIED, WEAKENED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:16:- **p21-tighter-than-full-pressure.md** — **NEW (E004).** P_k^{21} has LESS CZ slack than the full pressure: 1.7-3.9x vs 7.6-17.5x at q=2. The bottleneck piece's RHS tensor (u_below x u_below) is smoother/more structured. P22 and P23 have progressively more slack. CZ bound is tightest precisely where it matters most. Pressure decomposition verified to machine precision (<1.1e-15). [VERIFIED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:17:- **tran-yu-galilean-invariance-orthogonal.md** — **NEW (E003).** Tran-Yu program (5 papers, 2015-2021) on pressure moderation and Galilean invariance is ORTHOGONAL to De Giorgi bottleneck. Different energy functionals (global L^q vs level-set), different pressure objects (full p vs P_k^{21}), Galilean boost doesn't help P_k^{21}. Classification: better constant only, not better exponent. Grade C (not applicable). Two potentially useful ideas: nonlinear depletion at velocity maxima, velocity-pressure anti-correlation. [VERIFIED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:18:- **pressure-galilean-invariance.md** — **NEW (E003).** Pressure Poisson equation is exactly Galilean-invariant for incompressible flow (div u = 0 kills cross-terms). CZ bound ||p||_{L^q} <= C_q||u||_{L^{2q}}^2 unchanged by any constant-velocity frame shift. Fundamental reason Galilean boosts cannot improve the CZ bound on P_k^{21}. [VERIFIED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:19:- **choi-vasseur-2014-decomposition.md** — **NEW (E005).** Choi-Vasseur (2014, AIHP) three-way decomposition P = P_{1,k} + P_{2,k} + P_3 with P_3 absorbed into time-dependent truncation level. Achieves beta = 7/6 (weaker than 4/3, sufficient for their purpose). Does NOT bypass P_k^{21} bottleneck — the local pressure P_{2,k} still contains the CZ-limited non-divergence term. Technical simplification, not exponent improvement. [VERIFIED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:20:- **post-2007-beta-landscape.md** — **NEW (E005).** Comprehensive survey: NO paper since 2007 has attempted or claimed to improve beta beyond 4/3 in De Giorgi NS iteration. Community moved orthogonally: higher derivatives (CV14, Vasseur-Yang 2021), alternative regularity frameworks (epsilon-regularity, concentration), and extensions to other equations. The 4/3 barrier is untouched. [VERIFIED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:22:- **vorticity-degiorgi-universal-barrier.md** — **NEW (E008).** Vasseur-Yang (2021) applies De Giorgi iteration to pressure-free variable v. New 4/3 bottleneck from trilinear form (1/2 + 5/6 = 4/3), independent of pressure. **E009: "universality" is induction from 2 examples, not theorem — but two independent mechanisms both hitting 4/3 is suggestive. Proof of universality remains open.** [VERIFIED, clarified]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:27:- **chebyshev-universality-and-model-pde-comparison.md** — **NEW (S2-E003).** Universal formula beta = 1 + s/n for De Giorgi recursion exponent (Brigati-Mouhot 2025 confirms). Verified across 9 model PDEs: Burgers (beta=2), 2D NS (3/2), 3D NS (4/3), 4D NS (5/4), MHD (4/3), SQG direct (5/4), SQG extension (4/3), fractional NS alpha=5/4 (17/12), fractional NS alpha=3/2 (3/2). Chebyshev step NOT independently improvable — 6 routes ruled out or circular (improving L^{10/3} to L^4 requires H^{5/4} = Lions threshold). SQG success mechanism: drift is multiplicative (BMO^{-1} constant), not additional U power; commutator structure, not Chebyshev improvement. Open question: does div(u)=0 improve level-set distribution? (no paper addresses; appears genuinely open). MHD confirmed beta=4/3 (He-Xin 2005). Fractional NS: De Giorgi misses Lions regularity by alpha gap (5/4 vs 3/2). [VERIFIED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:28:- **compensated-compactness-commutator-obstruction.md** — **NEW (S2-E004).** Compensated compactness / commutator route to improving beta DEFINITIVELY CLOSED. Three-layer obstruction: (1) no div-curl structure — truncation breaks div(u)=0 with 0.07-0.14 compressibility; (2) commutator remainder dominates (61% of P^{21}, 18x at high frequencies); (3) CRW vacuous for bounded u^{below}. SQG-NS structural gap: scalar vs vector, linear vs quadratic, first-order vs second-order. Informal theorem: beta = 4/3 sharp within energy+Sobolev+CZ(+commutator/CLMS)+Chebyshev class. Div-free truncation topologically impossible. Four remaining directions identified. [COMPUTED, CONJECTURED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:31:- **non-cz-pressure-routes-tool-independence.md** — **NEW (S2-E006).** Three non-CZ pressure routes: IBP beta=1 (WORSE by 1/3), H^1/BMO beta=4/3 (MATCHES via different mechanism), CRW beta<=1 (confirms S2-E004). CZ consolidation gain = exactly 1/3. Beta = 4/3 is TOOL-INDEPENDENT — locked to NS quadratic structure, not analytical method. CZ becomes loose at high k (ratio 0.2->92 from k=2 to k=5). 12 published approaches surveyed, none achieve beta > 4/3. Two genuinely untested: Wolf local decomposition, Tran-Yu depletion. DNS confirms CZ 2-3x tighter than direct at low k, both overestimate by 5-20x. [COMPUTED, CONJECTURED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/INDEX.md:33:- **chebyshev-sharpness-constant-field-extremizer.md** — **NEW (S2-E008).** Chebyshev bound PROVABLY TIGHT for div-free fields: constant field u_n = (lambda+1/n, 0, 0) achieves ratio -> 1. Div-free constrains direction not magnitude. L^2 and H^1 constraints improve by constant factor only (10-200x), never exponent. De Giorgi truncation also tight. All 4 chain steps now confirmed individually tight under NS constraints. beta = 4/3 rigorously SHARP within De Giorgi-Vasseur framework. SDP formalization unnecessary — analytic extremizer is elementary. Closes open question from S2-E001 (direction a) and S2-E003 (div-free level-set distribution). [VERIFIED]
