execution/instances/vasseur-pressure/strategies/strategy-001/explorations/exploration-009/REPORT.md:63:**Partially survives, with important caveats.** The measurement IS what it IS — the CZ tightness ratio for P_k^{21} on smooth periodic DNS solutions is k-independent. This is a valid empirical fact. But the inference "therefore the CZ bound on P_k^{21} has no room for improvement in the De Giorgi proof" is NOT supported by this data. The proof operates in the limit of near-singular solutions, which DNS cannot access.
