execution/instances/vasseur-pressure/strategies/strategy-001/explorations/exploration-008/REPORT-SUMMARY.md:13:**However, a new 4/3 bottleneck appears.** The recurrence is Uₖ ≤ Cᵏ U_{k-1}^{min{4/3, 5/3 − 2/(3p₃)}}. The 4/3 comes not from pressure but from the interior trilinear form: ‖∇(βₖv)‖_{L²} · U_{k-1}^{5/6} = U_{k-1}^{1/2+5/6} = U_{k-1}^{4/3}. One derivative costs U^{1/2}; two nonlinear velocity-scale factors cost U^{5/6}. This is a manifestation of the quadratic nonlinearity itself.
