- The library does **not** contain Tao’s averaged-NS pressure equation in explicit form. What it does contain is the high-level consequence: Tao’s `averaged NS` can blow up, so any regularity proof must use the **specific algebraic structure** of the NS nonlinearity, not just energy-level or generic De Giorgi-style structure ([`post-2007-beta-landscape.md`](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/post-2007-beta-landscape.md#L41), [`s2-adversarial-review-beta-four-thirds.md`](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/s2-adversarial-review-beta-four-thirds.md#L21)).
- For the harmonic/far-field question, the local library has **ordinary Vasseur-pressure** material, not Tao-averaged material: it says the far-field pressure is harmonic on the local cube `Q_k` and decays by Harnack, but I found **no statement that this harmonic structure survives Tao’s averaged construction** ([`h1-pressure-dead-end.md`](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/h1-pressure-dead-end.md#L38)).
