+# Meta Note: Exploration 001
+
+## What worked
+
+- Starting with a decomposition audit was the right move. It surfaced the precise mismatch between the mission's loophole wording and Vasseur's actual pressure split before any Tao-filter work.
+- The receptionist query was useful because it pointed directly to the Proposition 3 audit and H^1 dead-end note, which were the two sources needed to reconcile the notation.
+
+## What to carry forward
+
+- When a surviving lead is described in different vocabularies across predecessor missions, force an explicit notation reconciliation before launching a falsification pass.
+- For pressure questions in Navier-Stokes, distinguish carefully between:
+  - Vasseur's nonlocal harmonic term `P_k1`,
+  - Vasseur's bad local term `P_k21`,
+  - any later Wolf-style or kernel-based far/near decomposition.
+- Treat phrases like "far-field term `P_k21`" as a red-flag shorthand that may hide a decomposition mismatch.
+
+## Execution note
+
+- The launched explorer exited after writing only a report skeleton. Recovery was straightforward because the exploration was synthesis-heavy and the required local sources were already identified. For future runs of similar tasks, a tighter source preload may reduce this failure mode.
+
