+- `Rot_{i,ω}` are spatial rotations,
+- `m_{i,ω}(D)` are order-zero Fourier multipliers,
+- the averaging also includes dilations in the final version of the paper.
+
+- [VERIFIED] Tao preserves cancellation:
+
+```text
+⟨\tilde B(u,u), u⟩ = 0.
+```
+
+### 2.3 What replaces `-Δp = ∂i∂j(u_i u_j)`?
+
+- [VERIFIED] Tao's averaged equation is written only in the projected bilinear-operator form `Δu + \tilde B(u,u)`.
+- [CHECKED] The ordinary scalar pressure law is **not** presented as a preserved local identity in the averaged model.
+- [CHECKED] The closest replacement is an averaged projected nonlinearity, not a local Poisson pressure determined by the instantaneous tensor `u ⊗ u`.
+
+So the correct answer is:
+
+```text
+ordinary NS:  -Δp = ∂i∂j(u_i u_j)
+averaged NS:  no canonical local scalar pressure law of that form survives;
+              the nonlinearity is absorbed into the averaged projected operator \tilde B.
+```
+
+## 3. Harmonic Far-Field Comparison
+
+### 3.1 Ordinary NS / Vasseur split
+
+In ordinary NS:
+
+- one has the local Poisson pressure law,
+- one can split pressure into near and far pieces on a local ball/cylinder,
+- the far part is harmonic on the local region because its source is outside.
+
+This is the structural basis of the loophole.
+
+### 3.2 Why Tao's averaging changes the picture
+
+Rotations and dilations alone would preserve the harmonic character of a locally harmonic function under geometric pullback. But Tao's averaging also uses **order-zero Fourier multipliers** on the inputs and output.
+
+- [CHECKED] Those multipliers are nonlocal.
+- [CHECKED] Nonlocal multipliers do not preserve **local** harmonicity in the sense the loophole needs, because they mix values from outside the local region back into the region.
+- [CHECKED] Thus even if one decomposed each inner NS term into near/far pressure pieces before averaging, the averaged output would no longer be a clean harmonic far-field component on the working cylinder.
+
+### 3.3 Consequence for the loophole
+
+The loophole requires:
+
+1. a scalar pressure obeying a local Poisson law,
+2. a near/far split,
+3. a far piece harmonic on `Q_k`,
+4. Harnack/oscillation control of that harmonic piece.
+
+Tao's averaged construction keeps only the high-level cancellation and harmonic-analysis estimates. It does **not** preserve this local elliptic decomposition in a usable form.
+
+## 4. Bottleneck Replacement Analysis
+
+### 4.1 Old bottleneck
+
+Ordinary Vasseur bottleneck:
+
+```text
+I_k ≤ ||P_{k21}||_{L^q} ||d_k||_{L^2} ||1_{v_k>0}||_{L^{2q/(q-2)}}
+    ≤ C_q C^k U_{k-1}^{4/3 - 5/(3q)}.
+```
+
+### 4.2 What replaces it in Tao's averaged model
+
+- [CHECKED] There is no directly corresponding `P_{k21}` obtained from a local pressure split.
+- [CHECKED] The bottleneck is more primitive: the averaged model keeps only the coarse bilinear operator structure and loses the local pressure geometry that the loophole hopes to exploit.
+- [CHECKED] So the "new bottleneck" is not another harmonic-pressure term; it is the disappearance of the very mechanism being proposed.
+
+This is exactly the kind of NS-specific structure Tao says a successful proof must use.
+
+### 4.3 Strongest counterargument
+
+One could argue that because every integrand inside the average comes from an ordinary NS-type bilinear term, perhaps one can average the far-field harmonic pieces termwise and still recover a useful harmonic far-field object.
+
+- [CHECKED] That argument fails at the local level because the order-zero Fourier multipliers act nonlocally.
+- [CHECKED] Global commutation with `Δ` is not enough; the loophole needs **local harmonicity on `Q_k`**, not merely formal compatibility with the Laplacian on all of space.
+
+## 5. Verdict Table
+
+| Item | Ordinary NS | Averaged NS | Verdict |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| Pressure law | `-Δp = ∂i∂j(u_i u_j)` | `∂_t u = Δu + \tilde B(u,u)` with averaged projected bilinear operator | [VERIFIED] changed |
+| Canonical local scalar pressure | Yes | Not in the same local Poisson form | [CHECKED] lost |
+| Near/far split with harmonic far-field on `Q_k` | Yes, in principle | Not preserved in a clean local form after multiplier averaging | [CHECKED] lost |
+| Harnack-ready harmonic component | Available in the loophole picture | No sourced surviving analogue found | [CHECKED] absent |
+| Overall classification | Loophole can be formulated | Loophole structure is not preserved | `Tao-incompatible` |
+
+## 6. Recommended Next Move
+
+- [CHECKED] Because the verdict is `Tao-incompatible`, the Tao filter does **not** close the mission.
+- [CHECKED] The next step should be a minimal falsification model: exhibit the smallest explicit harmonic far-field pressure configuration and test whether its pairing can ever become `U_k`-dependent rather than fixed at energy scale.
+
+## 7. Sources
+
+| Claim / formula | Source | Status |
+|---|---|---|
+| `B(u,v) = -(1/2) P[(u·∇)v + (v·∇)u]` and abstract formulation `∂_t u = Δu + B(u,u)` | Tao 2016 JAMS PDF snippet stored via AMS search result; repository prior Tao note | [VERIFIED] |
+| Averaged operator `\tilde B` as average of rotations, dilations, and order-zero multipliers applied to `B` | repository prior Tao note in navier-stokes exploration-005 report | [VERIFIED] |
+| Tao's structural implication: generic energy/harmonic-analysis information is insufficient | `post-2007-beta-landscape.md`; `s2-adversarial-review-beta-four-thirds.md` | [VERIFIED] |
+| Need for local harmonic far-field structure from exploration 001 | exploration-001 report | [VERIFIED] |
+| Loss of local harmonicity under output Fourier multipliers | present deduction from Tao's averaged-operator formula | [CHECKED] |
+
+## 8. Execution Note
+
+- The launched explorer remained unfinished while gathering Tao primary-source material. This report completes the Tao filter directly from the sourced bilinear-operator formula plus the local mission context.
