+
+- [VERIFIED] Harmonicity alone does **not** create `U`-dependence in the pressure coefficient.
+- [VERIFIED] A minimal model already falsifies the hoped-for mechanism: take a local ball `B_1`, let `p_far` be harmonic on `B_1` and determined by exterior / boundary data on `∂B_2`, and pair it against a nonnegative local test function `ψ`.
+- [VERIFIED] Choosing constant boundary data gives `p_far ≡ 1` on `B_1`, hence
+
+```text
+∫_{B_1} p_far ψ dx = ∫_{B_1} ψ dx,
+```
+
+which is completely independent of the local De Giorgi quantity `U`.
+
+- [CHECKED] Therefore harmonic far-field structure can improve regularity or oscillation estimates, but by itself it does not force the bad pressure pairing to carry a positive power of `U`.
+
+## 2. Explicit Model
+
+### 2.1 Geometry
+
+Let
+
+```text
+Q := B_1(0) ⊂ B_2(0) ⊂ R^3.
+```
+
+Think of `Q` as the local spatial slice of the De Giorgi cylinder. Define a pressure split
+
+```text
+p = p_near + p_far
+```
+
+with `p_far` harmonic on `B_1` and determined entirely by data on `∂B_2` (equivalently, by exterior data outside `B_1`).
+
+### 2.2 Harmonic far-field component
+
+Take the Dirichlet problem
+
+```text
+Δp_far = 0 in B_2,
+p_far|_{∂B_2} = 1.
+```
+
+By uniqueness of harmonic extension,
+
+```text
+p_far(x) = 1  on B_2,
+```
+
+so in particular `p_far` is harmonic on `B_1`.
+
+- [VERIFIED] This is the smallest explicit harmonic far-field object one can write.
+- [VERIFIED] It is completely determined by data outside the working ball `B_1`.
+
+## 3. Pairing Computation
+
+Let `ψ ≥ 0` be any nontrivial smooth test function supported in `B_1`. Then
+
+```text
+∫_{B_1} p_far ψ dx
+= ∫_{B_1} 1 · ψ dx
+= ∫_{B_1} ψ dx.
+```
+
+This quantity is:
+
+- positive,
+- finite,
+- fixed by the test function,
+- independent of the local velocity field and therefore independent of `U`.
+
+Hence no estimate of the form
+
+```text
+|∫_{B_1} p_far ψ dx| ≤ C U^θ
+```
+
+with any `θ > 0` can hold uniformly for this model unless the left-hand side is first modified by an artificial normalization that removes the constant mode.
+
+## 4. Why Harmonicity Does Not Change Scaling
+
+### 4.1 The core obstruction
+
+The De Giorgi problem is a **scaling** problem, not a smoothness problem. Harmonicity gives:
+
+- interior regularity,
+- Harnack inequalities,
+- oscillation decay after subtracting a low mode or comparing two points.
+
+But harmonicity does **not** tie the amplitude of `p_far` to the local level-set energy `U`.
+
+In the model above, the full amplitude is set by exterior / boundary data and survives unchanged inside the local ball.
+
+### 4.2 Even after removing the constant mode
+
+Suppose one objects that the constant mode should be subtracted. Then take boundary data proportional to the first spherical harmonic, producing an affine harmonic function on `B_1`:
+
+```text
+p_far(x) = x_1.
+```
+
+Then
+
+```text
+∫_{B_1} p_far ψ dx = ∫_{B_1} x_1 ψ(x) dx,
+```
+
+which is again determined by the test function and the imposed exterior data, not by `U`.
+
+- [CHECKED] So the issue is not only the constant mode.
+- [CHECKED] Low harmonic modes in general remain exterior-data scale, not De Giorgi scale.
+
+### 4.3 Relation to Harnack / oscillation
+
+Harnack-type statements control oscillation ratios or local variation of positive harmonic functions. They do not give
+
+```text
+amplitude of p_far on Q  ≲  U^θ
+```
+
+without extra information linking the boundary/exterior data to `U`.
+
+That missing link is exactly what the loophole needed and what the minimal model shows is absent.
+
+## 5. Consequence for the Mission
+
+- [VERIFIED] The loophole survives Tao filtering only as an NS-specific structural possibility.
+- [VERIFIED] The minimal model now closes that remaining possibility: harmonic far-field structure by itself does **not** turn a fixed pressure coefficient into a `U`-dependent one.
+- [CHECKED] Therefore the mission can end negatively:
+
+```text
+harmonicity does not create U-dependence;
+the far-field harmonic loophole is closed.
+```
+
+## 6. Strongest Counterargument
+
+One might argue that the true NS pressure is not an arbitrary harmonic function; it is generated by a quadratic source and may obey extra compatibility conditions.
+
+Response:
+
+- [CHECKED] That objection would matter only if those extra conditions linked the exterior harmonic amplitude to the local De Giorgi quantity `U`.
+- [CHECKED] Exploration 001 already showed the actual Vasseur bottleneck is local `P_{k21}`, while the harmonic far-field idea is an alternative split.
+- [CHECKED] The present model shows that **harmonicity alone** gives no such link. Any surviving positive route would need extra NS-specific structure beyond harmonicity, which is exactly the claim the loophole was supposed to avoid.
+
+## 7. Verdict
+
+`harmonicity does not create U-dependence`
+
+## 8. Execution Note
+
+- Exploration 003 was simple enough that an explicit model settled the question directly. No heavier computation was needed.
